Descrizione√à a herbaceous plant bienne, the stem of which is hairless and rather gleaned in the upper part, while it is felted on the bottom. The flowers are grouped in a racemic terminal which often leads lateral ramifications. They are yellow with petals spotted red blood. The plant may reach from 50 to 100 cm of height. The flowering period is from June to September.
Distribution and habitatIl mullein black is widespread in the temperate zones, and temperate-cold in Europe, with an area that extends from Spain to the Ukraine. You can find it in thin pastures and bushy meadows and edges of roads, from the lowlands up to about 1600 meters of altitude.
